Saint_Timothy\"}, {\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 0.6019988090368161, \"rank\": 0.66110042762844, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2023 Berlin marathon runner-up and newcomer Alexander Mutiso also made the cut.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9986510576306791, \"rank\": 0.0011872590270824604, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipchoge is bidding to become the first athlete to win three Olympic marathon golds following his successes at Rio in 2016 and Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999984001988, \"rank\": 1.5995742147692515e-09, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, he struggled to a10th place finish at the 2024 Tokyo Marathonbehind winner Kipruto (2:02:16) and Kiplagat (2:02:55).\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The race was taking place less than a month after world record-holderKelvin Kiptumdied when his car crashed into a tree in Kenya.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.337280355636632e-26, \"text\": \"Ken